Absolutely! Here's how to enhance your Dashboard so that:

‚úÖ The comment is shown in the table for each task.

‚úÖ Users can filter tasks by keyword (in any field including comment, status, file names, etc.)

‚úÖ 1. Update the Dashboard Table to Include Comments
In dashboard.html:
A. Add a new <th> for the Comment:
html
Copy
Edit
<th>Comment</th>
B. Add a new <td> in the row for each task:
html
Copy
Edit
<td>{{ task.comment or '' }}</td>
Now your table structure might look like:

html
Copy
Edit
<thead>
  <tr>
    <th>Task ID</th>
    <th>Submitted Time</th>
    <th>Input Metadata</th>
    <th>Using RAG</th>
    <th>Status</th>
    <th>Result</th>
    <th>Log File</th>
    <th>Comment</th>
    <th>Action</th>
  </tr>
</thead>
‚úÖ 2. Add a Keyword Filter Input Box (Client-Side)
Place this above the table:

html
Copy
Edit
<input type="text" id="taskFilterInput" placeholder="Filter tasks..." style="margin-bottom: 10px; padding: 5px; width: 300px;">
‚úÖ 3. Add JavaScript to Filter Rows Based on Keyword
Add this at the end of the file (below the table):

html
Copy
Edit
<script>
  const filterInput = document.getElementById("taskFilterInput");
  filterInput.addEventListener("input", function () {
    const keyword = this.value.toLowerCase();
    const rows = document.querySelectorAll("table tbody tr");

    rows.forEach(row => {
      const rowText = row.textContent.toLowerCase();
      row.style.display = rowText.includes(keyword) ? "" : "none";
    });
  });
</script>
‚úÖ Final Output
‚úèÔ∏è Users see the comment for each task in the dashboard.

üîç Typing in the filter box will instantly hide/show rows based on matches in:

Task ID

Status

RAG selection

File names

üî• Comments!

